column1: Do you agree to the above terms? By clicking Yes, you consent that you are willing to participate in this anonymous survey.
column2: Please select your position in the department
column3: In total, How long have you been a Law Enforcement Professional or Police Officer ?
column4: Do you know what EAP (Employee Assistance Program) services are available to you?
column5: Do you know how to access EAP (Employee Assistance Program) services?
column6: Please select how likely you are to use EAP (Employee Assistance Program) services?
column7: Do you know what Peer Support services are available to you?
column8: Do you know who your Peer Support team is?
column9: Do you know how to access Peer Support services?
column10: Please select how likely are you to use Peer Support?
column11: I feel comfortable confiding with my Peer Support members.
column12: I am interested in attending inservices for coping with stress and other mental health skills.
column13: How likely would you be to participate in webinars or online workshops instead of in person training's?
column14: Resources and tips to help cope would be helpful during shift briefings.
column15: In terms of coping, how helpful would you find an Officer Wellness Training during your first year in the department?
column16: If you were offered workshops about diet and nutrition how likely would you be to attend and participate?
column17: If you were offered workshops about exercise and fitness how likely would you be to attend and participate?
column18: If you and your family were offered family skills workshops how likely would you be to attend and participate?
column19: If you and your family were offered access to a department support group how likely would you be to attend and participate?
column20: Would you find workshops about healthy relationships or marriage skills beneficial?
column21: If you were offered classes about personal finances how likely would you be to attend and participate?
column22: If you were offered classes about mindfulness or meditation how likely would you be to attend and participate?
column23: If you were offered resiliency training how likely would you be to attend and participate?
column24: Would being partially reimbursed for personal wellness expenses (ex: counseling services, health training, wealth management, fitness events… etc.) increase the likelihood you would utilize such services?
column25: In what way do you feel your work as a law enforcement professional has impacted your spiritual beliefs?
column26: To what extent do you feel your religious or spiritual beliefs have been impacted by your work as a law enforcement professional?
column27: To what extent does any connection to a spiritual being help you get through hard times?
column28: To what extent does any connection to a spiritual being help you to tolerate stress?
column29: Do you know what Department Spiritual Support services are available to you?
column30: How likely are you to utilize the department Chaplain for spiritual guidance and comfort?
column31: Finding it difficult to separate work from my personal life.
column32: Trouble falling, staying asleep or sleeping too much.
column33: Did you struggle with sleep prior to becoming a  police officer or law enforcement professional?
column34: Feeling distant or cut off from people outside  law enforcement.
column37: Experiencing distressing memories of job related experiences.
column38: Having physical reactions (ex: heart pounding, trouble breathing, sweating) when something reminds you of a stressful job related experience.
column39: Feeling irritable or having angry outbursts.
column40: Intense anger that is directed toward others.
column41: Intense anger that is directed toward myself.
column43: How frequently are you experiencing suicidal thoughts?
column44: I don’t know where to get help.
column45: It would be difficult getting time off work for treatment.
column47: People who need help are weak and ineffective.
column48: If members in my team found out I was seeking mental health services, they might have less confidence in me.
column49: If my shift leadership found out I was seeking mental health services, they might treat me differently.
column50: Evidence of mental health care in my medical records could harm my career.
column52: I can think of other law enforcement professionals or officers in the department who might need mental health treatment.
column53: At times I have wondered if I need mental health treatment.
column54: How do you deal with stress after a hard shift? Check ALL that apply.
column55: How often do you drink more than 4 alcohol drinks in a single day and more than 14 alcohol drinks in a week?  (A drink is defined as: 12 ounces of beer, 5 ounces of wine, or 1.5 ounces of spirits)
